    "properties_description": "The main therapeutic properties of Curcuma longa are its antioxidant activities, which involve the neutralization of free radicals and the prevention of oxidative stress, thereby protecting cells from damage. The anti-inflammatory properties of Curcuma longa, facilitated by bioactive compounds such as curcumin and demethoxycurcumin, reduce the production of pro-inflammatory enzymes and cytokines, thereby alleviating conditions like arthritis. Additionally, the antimicrobial properties of Curcuma longa, attributed to volatile oils like cineole and borneol, inhibit the growth of pathogens and prevent infections. The analgesic properties of Curcuma longa, associated with the inhibition of pain-producing enzymes, provide relief from pain and discomfort. Furthermore, the neuroprotective properties of Curcuma longa, linked to the reduction of beta-amyloid plaques and neuroinflammation, may help in the prevention and treatment of neurodegenerative diseases.",
