    "constituents_description": "The most important healing constituents of Curcuma longa are curcumin, demethoxycurcumin, bisdemethoxycurcumin, curcumenol, and turmerone. Curcumin is the primary bioactive compound, possessing potent antioxidant, anti-inflammatory, and anti-cancer properties due to its ability to inhibit NF-kappa B and COX-2 enzymes. Demethoxycurcumin and bisdemethoxycurcumin, two other curcuminoids, have been found to have anti-inflammatory and antioxidant activities, albeit to a lesser extent than curcumin. Curcumenol, a sesquiterpene alcohol, exhibits anti-inflammatory and immunomodulatory effects, while turmerone, a sesquiterpene, has been shown to have neuroprotective properties and promote the growth of neural stem cells. These constituents contribute to the therapeutic benefits of Curcuma longa in treating various diseases, including arthritis, diabetes, and neurodegenerative disorders.",
