    "preparations_description": "The main herbal preparations of Curcuma longa are derived from its rhizomes and are used for their medicinal properties. Turmeric powder, made from dried and ground rhizomes, is a common preparation used in cooking and as a dietary supplement. Golden milk, a mixture of turmeric powder, milk, and honey, is often consumed for its anti-inflammatory and antioxidant properties. Turmeric tea, made by infusing turmeric powder in hot water, is used to alleviate digestive issues and reduce inflammation. Turmeric capsules, containing a concentrated extract of the rhizomes, are commonly used to treat conditions such as arthritis and other inflammatory diseases due to the high bioavailability of curcumin, its active compound.",
