    "side_effects_description": "The possible side effects of using Curcuma longa improperly include experiencing diarrhea, nausea, abdominal pain, and potentially developing liver damage. This is due to the high levels of curcuminoids, which can cause gastrointestinal irritation when taken in excessive amounts. Consuming high doses of Curcuma longa can stimulate digestive enzymes, leading to increased gut motility and resulting in diarrhea and abdominal pain. In some cases, excessive curcumin intake may also cause liver toxicity, as curcumin can increase the production of liver enzymes, which may be a sign of liver damage. If not used properly, Curcuma longa can have adverse effects, particularly in individuals with pre-existing liver conditions or those taking medications that interact with curcumin."
